4 Searching
***********

mu4e is fully search-based; this means that all the lists of messages
you see, are the result of some query. Even if you 'jump to a folder',
in fact you are executing a search query for messages that happen to
have the property of being in a certain folder.

   Queries normally return only up to `mu4e-search-results-limit' (which
defaults to 1000) results. You get _all_ results when you prefix your
search commands (such as with `mu4e-headers-search',
`mu4e-headers-search-bookmark',
`mu4e-headers-search-bookmark-edit-first' and
`mu4e-headers-jump-to-maildir' with `C-u'.

   This limit was introduced in earlier versions of mu4e, where emacs
could become slow when there were many matches. This is no longer the
case (post mu4e version 0.9.8.3), but since it is still faster to limit
the number of matches, the limit remains.

